<font color="#FF0000">EX-WIVES AND TENNESSEE</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jul 29 13:22:22 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
Talk about ex-wives, mine made a complaint to the captain that I was not writing enough. Had the Red Cross and every humanitarian social organization check up on me.  Captain send me to the DaNang Marrs station to say &quot;over&quot; each time we spoke on the radio.  <br>
I finally wrote but she got pissed off because I wrote to her from the bush. The only thing I had to write on was C-rat toilet tissue. <br>
I think she wanted verification that I was still alive or the GI benefits if I had been killed.<br>
Almost moved to Tennessee last year, but like re-enlistment. I thought about it, laughed about it and forgot about it.<br>
I have five daughters and I've heard from those that have moved here from there, that everyone is related to each other in that state for some reason.<br><br>

<p><code>--   (Cook Barela) </code><p>


